HEADWORD: Trachyte
<hw>Tra"chyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ rough,
rugged: cg. F. <ets>trachyte</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An
igneous rock, usually light gray in color and breaking with a rough
surface. It consists chiefly of orthoclase feldspar with sometimes
hornblende and mica.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

